‘unskilled.’, iv 3, 6-7 u caindä va vāri starCk) da(m)di akalāśca hīri yudai ‘and. as to how many are the shares, so unskilfully you have acted.’; iv 3-8-9 ttadī (daṃdi) akalāścauñä ya ‘it was only through such lack of skill’. Seekala- ‘excellent’.
